On American Business Women's Day, the article celebrates the contributions of women in transforming the landscape of businesses in the United States. It recognizes these women as role models for future generations and highlights the economic benefits of empowering women. The article mentions that the unemployment rate for women reached its lowest level in 1953 and that women now make up a majority of the labor force. It also acknowledges the increasing number of women leading Fortune 500 companies and owning their own businesses, generating significant revenue. The article emphasizes the importance of female-led businesses in rebuilding communities and creating jobs in the aftermath of the coronavirus pandemic. The article also mentions the efforts of the current administration to expand opportunities for women in business, such as providing paid parental leave and increasing the Child Tax Credit. The article concludes by recommitting to promoting and empowering women in the workplace, as it is seen as an investment in future economic growth and prosperity.